content:
A method which I have used before was to convert an MP4 file (feasable if only a handful of seconds)to a GIF file. Then the individual images can be imported into a pwad with Slade3.
The animation can then be accomplished either with ANIMATED or ANIMDEFS, or scripted

SetLineTexture(line1, SIDE_FRONT, TEXTURE_MIDDLE, "image001");
delay ( time);
and repeated for the number of images.

 
As a consequence, however, the file size will be enormous. For example my pwad Agility_Course
